298
00:27:25,201 --> 00:27:29,904
[SPEAKER_02]: A couple of things for the roll call.

299
00:27:30,304 --> 00:27:38,329
[SPEAKER_02]: My recollection is that we advised from the Winchester line to Lawrence Road for the phase one and Lawrence Road supposed to be phase two.

300
00:27:38,849 --> 00:27:44,112
[SPEAKER_02]: In terms of the, yeah, it's basically a re-marking of the bike lanes with the current

301
00:27:44,772 --> 00:27:47,434
[SPEAKER_02]: Standards in the industry with the buffer, right?

302
00:27:47,815 --> 00:27:55,881
[SPEAKER_02]: So the old one in the 2015-16 version of the bike lane up there, it just had a single line with the symbol in there against the curb.

303
00:27:56,401 --> 00:28:10,813
[SPEAKER_02]: And all we did was push that single line closest to the curb and add the buffer striping that's common going back to that one pager that, you know, there are many, as Sergeant Rogers pointed out, there's two sides to this issue.

304
00:28:11,972 --> 00:28:20,740
[SPEAKER_02]: just as many people, if not more, say they wanted the whole corridor to be the buffer and no parking at all, because it's the safest possible scenario for cyclists.

305
00:28:21,140 --> 00:28:24,703
[SPEAKER_02]: So we're trying to be reasonable and compromise wherever we can.

306
00:28:24,723 --> 00:28:33,610
[SPEAKER_02]: And it is similar with, you are correct about that, we actually reached out, Medford reached out to Winchester to add a bike lane to say, hey, we're doing one, if you want to do one.

307
00:28:33,791 --> 00:28:36,373
[SPEAKER_02]: So they added theirs after the fact.

308
00:28:36,973 --> 00:28:38,695
[SPEAKER_02]: But using the parking data,

309
00:28:39,815 --> 00:28:46,080
[SPEAKER_02]: We took that into account and saw that there was less than 2% usage on this northern portion, plus many of it already had the bike lane.

310
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:55,308
[SPEAKER_02]: And then the southern portion wasn't much more, it was only like 16%, but that's when there was a compromise made to do the bike lanes next to the one-sided parking.

311
00:28:56,829 --> 00:29:02,874
[SPEAKER_02]: I can bring up Street View to show what it used to look like, but first I'll quickly show the one-pager again.

312
00:29:03,354 --> 00:29:04,155
[SPEAKER_02]: So the cyclists

313
00:29:04,855 --> 00:29:14,724
[SPEAKER_02]: advocates and safety advocates want this bottom scenario where there's a bike lane next to the curb, a buffer with a vertical piece separating them from a car.

314
00:29:15,484 --> 00:29:31,998
[SPEAKER_02]: What we have on Winthrop Street is this situation where the bike lane is next to the curb with the painted buffer without the vertical piece, and then sometimes there's a bike lane next to a curb, and then there's a situation not shown here where we have it in the southern portion where the bike lane is next to a

315
00:29:34,871 --> 00:29:40,575
[SPEAKER_02]: which a lot of folks on the bicycle side of it will argue that it's unsafe and they don't necessarily want that.

316
00:29:40,595 --> 00:29:44,697
[SPEAKER_02]: So we're trying to accommodate a lot of needs, and we do have a complete streets policy.

317
00:29:46,058 --> 00:30:00,949
[SPEAKER_02]: In terms of the comments about volume or people using it or not, basically it's a little bit of a, if you build it, they will come scenario where if you have like just a couple blocks of a bike lane, it may not have gotten usage, but once you have a whole corridor, we're actually seeing

318
00:30:01,419 --> 00:30:02,340
[SPEAKER_02]: more and more usage.

319
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:10,606
[SPEAKER_02]: So over time, we actually got thank yous from people that, you know, travel, commute to Boston as far as Uber.

320
00:30:11,487 --> 00:30:13,128
[SPEAKER_02]: Not that we're doing this for those folks.

321
00:30:13,548 --> 00:30:17,351
[SPEAKER_02]: It's just an example of other people that are feeling positive.

322
00:30:17,371 --> 00:30:18,872
[SPEAKER_02]: But I'll go to the street view.

323
00:30:18,892 --> 00:30:20,674
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll see if I could find this.

